post_text:
This just in! The USDA has extended the free-meal program into this school year. For Cassville students, that means ALL students in EVERY building will not be charged for breakfast or lunch. This program will continue until funds are depleted. We will update you with information as we find out.
A la carte items, snack milk and extra milks still require payment.

Please note, if you have an unpaid balance from previous school years, those balances will remain. Give us a call or visit our website to make a payment.

post_text:
Support the Cassville Music Performing Arts this year by purchasing our first 2020-2021 School Calendar.

The calendar includes the official district calendar, football schedule, and concert schedules for the music performing arts groups.

Each month features one of the vocal and instrumental K-12 music programs at Cassville. The calendar also includes concert choir, concert band, show choir, marching band, winter guard, the kid kat choir, and the 3rd grade elementary music program.

The calendars are $10.00 each. 100% of the costs will go to support the programs featured in the calendar.

You can contact Mrs. Reedy at lreedy@cassville.k12.mo.us, Mr. Surber at dsurber@cassville.k12.mo.us, or any Cassville Music Department Staff or student.

NOTICE TO THE CLASS OF 2015:

Cassville High School will be purging the cumulative school records for the graduating class of 2015. If you would like to have your records, you must pick them up in person at the high school between 8:30 a.m. and 3:30 p.m. in August. If you are unable to pick them up in person and would like someone to do it for you, we must have a signed request from you before we can release them.

post_text: Great surprise for three teachers today! Thank you, Cassville Education Fund, for making these grants (and surprises!) possible!
shared_text:
Cassville Community Foundation
May 20 at 7:41 PM ¬∑

The Cassville Education Fund was able to surprise three Cassville Public Schools teachers this morning as winners of the 2020 Education Fund grants.

A grant of $1,436 was presented to primary school librarian, Savannah Essary, for a subscription to the Scholastic Bookflix service.

A grant of $1,050 was presented to Tracie Greening and Morgan McDavid for novel sets for sixth grade English Language Arts Classes!

Congratulations and thank you to everyone who supports the Cassville Education Fund each year!

post_text:
Wildcats, this is tough. While we must all do our part to stay healthy, this news is hard for our students, staff and community. Please know you are loved and missed at Cassville R-IV.

Our doors will remain closed through the rest of the school year, however, we will continue to provide school-to-home learning resources and grab-and-go meal options.

MSHSAA has also announced the cancellation of the spring season due to students not being allowed into the school buildings for the remainder of the school year.

Continue to watch our website and social media pages for updates from our district.
shared_text:
Missouri Department of Elementary and Secondary Education
April 9 at 8:12 PM ¬∑

Missouri Governor Mike Parson announced in the Thursday, April 9 press briefing that Missouri schools will remain closed through this school year. DESE, along with several school superintendents from across the state, made the recommendation to Governor Mike Parson on April 9. Learn more about this announcement here in remarks by Commissioner of Education Margie Vandeven.

https://dese.mo.gov/sites/default/files/Gov-Closes-Schools-April-9.pdf

There is no higher priority for our entire Cassville R-IV School District family than the safety of our students, staff and communities. Based on guidance from the Barry and Lawrence County Health Departments and neighboring school districts, Cassville R-IV will dismiss for a Wellness Break March 17- April 3.

All events, activities (extra-curricular, co-curricular), and practices will be suspended/postponed during this time.

District administration will reassess the situation with local health departments and county school districts on or before April 3rd to determine when school will resume based on any new guidance.

Please continue to check our district website at cassville.k12.mo.us for updates and parent resources.

We will update the following link with information as it becomes available: https://cassville.socs.net/vnews/display.v/ART/5e6a895260cf6

Some of the topics discussed were High-Quality Assessments, Concepts of Standards-Based Learning and Teaching, Moments and Minutes, and The Power of Language, amongst many other topics.

We thank our summit committee members, speakers, teachers, and everyone involved who made this event possible.
